U.S. Naval Academy STEM Center for Education and Outreach's Dr. Angela Moran, the "Mother of USNA STEM," recently retired after 27 years of teaching! 

Dr. Moran is passionate about helping people reach their full potential and she not only taught and mentored midshipmen but also created #STEM programs for youth in underserved communities. She taught them about the endless possibilities of the world around them and encouraged everyone to believe in themselves.

#USNASTEM #WomeninSTEM

node.text:
Plebe Rates Competition 📓

One plebe per platoon is selected based on their knowledge of required #PlebeSummer rates to compete against one another in a spelling bee style competition.

Each plebe is asked a rate; if they respond correctly, they remain on stage.  If they respond incorrectly, they go back to their companies. 

Learning your rates and the spirit of competition are two major facets of the Plebe Summer experience, combined in this competition to produce a fun, team-oriented plebe event.

Where the White Works are ✨

White Works are the official plebe uniform for the duration of #PlebeSummer. 

White Works Echo features a Blue Rim shirt under the Jumper blouse and the Dixie Cup cover, and is the day to day uniform. 

White Works Alpha features a black neckerchief and a Combination Cover, and is worn for special occasions, including plebe parades. 

#UniformOfTheDay #USNA

Improvise. Adapt. Overcome.

For many plebes, #PlebeSummer is a challenge unlike any they have ever faced. 

At the end of this six weeks of training, plebes will appreciate the importance of mental, moral, and physical toughness in all aspects of duty and service. They will be prepared for the rigorous academic year that awaits them. 

#USNA #GoNavy #USNA2025

Normal is boring 💪

#PlebeSummer is not your normal college introduction. 

Plebes test their physical and mental endurance with activities like the Obstacle Course. This challenging sequence of logs, ropes and metal bars tests the strength, agility and cardiovascular endurance. 

#GetTough #GoNavy

📸: ENS Quinn Schneider
